WHO   — THE IDIOLECT STACK — the foundational model of PHONETIKOS
WHAT  — THE IDIOLECT STACK — the operating theory of PHONETIKOS: every voice = Culture×Location ⊕ Nurture ⊕ Generation.
WHERE — the three layers beneath every idiolect — the macro coordinate, the micro-location, and the generational globe  Framework inputs: variationist sociolinguistics — Labov, Trudgill, Eckert, Milroy; the apparent-time hypothesis; heritage-speaker & koineization studies  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because no two voices are identical: each is a stack of where you're from, who raised you and where, and when you came up.
HOW   — Culture×Location sets the base (rooted 1.0, or 0.5/0.5 hybrid); nurture / micro-location narrows it to a sociolect; the generational cultural-globe timestamps it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  A voice is a coordinate, a neighbourhood, and a timestamp — where you're from, who raised you, and when you came up.

